cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.PL, cs.EV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper discusses the application of an edge detection filter to images of sand dunes on Mars, which falls under the domain of computer vision.
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper uses the GIMP software to apply the Sobel filter, which is a graphics software, to the images of the sand dunes.
- cs.RO (Robotics): The study of sand dunes on Mars is relevant to robotics, as it can inform the design and operation of rovers and other robotic systems on the planet.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper may involve programming in order to apply the edge detection filter and analyze the images.
- cs.EV (Embedded Systems): The study of sand dunes on Mars may also be relevant to the development of embedded systems for space exploration.
